They had been arrested on Friday after a joint operation with the South African Police Service and the Department of Agriculture Forestry and Fisheries. The elaborate operation kicked off during early hours of Thursday morning when a 16-ton Scania truck was pulled over around Beaufort West in the Western Cape the Hawks said. The resultant search uncovered seven pallets of dried abalone (weighing 2.4 tons). Preliminary investigations linked the ownership of the truck to a business based in Boksburg near Johannesburg. The team searched the Gauteng business premises and found another 430.5kg of abalone hoarded in a shipment container.The suspects are believed to be heading a transnational abalone smuggling ring were subsequently arrested .The matter was postponed to November 28. TMG Digital